trends_and_observations: Several matchups were decided by unusually large individual RB performances (TreVeyon Henderson, Jonathan Taylor, Jahmyr Gibbs, De'Von Achane) — week skewed toward high RB upside.

Defenses and kickers had outsized impacts in multiple games (Seahawks D/ST 21.0, Broncos D/ST 16.0, Eagles D/ST 12.0, multiple kickers with multi-FG days and a few zero/low outings such as Brandon McManus 0.0 and Matt Prater 1.0).

A consistent theme: high-value points left on benches influenced several outcomes (notable benchings: Jared Goff 24.8; Baker Mayfield 22.92; Kimani Vidal 17.3; Tez Johnson 18.2; Brian Robinson Jr. 11.0).
Multiple starters (QBs and WRs) recorded significant underperformances vs projection (Justin Fields, Bo Nix, Jordan Love, Justin Jefferson, A.J. Brown), which swung projected outcomes.
A mix of BYEs and inactives appears across rosters and likely affected lineup decisions and weekly ceilings.
